# type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:225
msgid "Skipping Circular Path Tests"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:227
msgid ""
"The second (and most time-intensive) portion of the configuration startup "
"phase is the circular path check. In the example above, it took nearly a "
"minute to perform this step of the configuration verification."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:232
msgid ""
"What is the circular path check and why does it take so long? The circular "
"patch check is designed to ensure that you don't define any circular paths "
"in your host, host dependency, or service dependency definitions. If a "
"circular path existed in your config files, Nagios could end up in a "
"deadlock situation. The most likely reason for the check taking so long is "
"that I'm not using an efficient algorithm. A much more efficient algorithm "
"for detecting circular paths would be most welcomed.  Hint: That means all "
"you CompSci graduate students who have been emailing me about doing your "
"thesis on Nagios can contribute some code back.  :-)"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:243
msgid ""
"If you want to skip the circular path check when Nagios starts, you can add "
"the -x command line option like this:"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><screen>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"<prompt>linux:~ # </prompt><userinput>/usr/local/nagios/bin/nagios -xd /usr/local/nagios/etc/nagios.cfg</userinput>\n"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><important><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:249
msgid ""
"It is of utmost importance that you verify your configuration before "
"starting/restarting Nagios when skipping circular path checks.  Failure to "
"do so could lead to deadlocks in the Nagios logic. You have been warned."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:257
msgid "Putting It All Together"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:259
msgid ""
"Follow these steps if you want to make use of potential speedups from pre-"
"caching your configuration and skipping circular path checks."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:265
msgid ""
"Verify your configuration and create the precache file with the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para><screen>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:266
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"<prompt>linux:~ # </prompt><userinput>/usr/local/nagios/bin/nagios -vp /usr/local/nagios/etc/nagios.cfg</userinput>\n"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:272
msgid "Stop Nagios if it is currently running."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:276
msgid ""
"Start Nagios like so to use the precached config file and skip circular path "
"checks:"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para><screen>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"<prompt>linux:~ # </prompt><userinput>/usr/local/nagios/bin/nagios -uxd /usr/local/nagios/etc/nagios.cfg</userinput>\n"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:283
msgid ""
"When you modify your original configuration files in the future and need to "
"restart Nagios to make those changes take place, repeat step 1 to re-verify "
"your config and regenerate your cached config file. Once that is done you "
"can restart Nagios through the web interface or by sending a SIGHUP signal. "
"If you don't re-generate the precached object file, Nagios will continue to "
"use your old confguration because it is now reading from the precached file, "
"rather than your source configuration files."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><procedure><step><para>
#: SecurityAndPerformanceTuning/faststartup.xml:294
msgid "That's it! Enjoy the increased startup speed."
msgstr ""
